* bmp180 hardware profile

Before writing code, we must understand how the Linux Kernel sees this device:

Default I2C Address: 0x77.

The "Chip ID" Register: 0xD0. If you read this register, it should always return
0x55. This is the first test your driver should perform to verify it's talking
to the right hardware.

Control Register: 0xF4. You write to this to tell the chip to start a
temperature or pressure measurement.


